{
  "doc_id": "1692",
  "text": "A type 1 cap structure (m 7 GpppAmp) is added to the 5′ end of nascent genomes by NS5 which has guanylyltranferase as well as N7 and 2′O S-adenosyl methionine MTase activities in its N-terminal domain [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ). The NS5 MTase interacts with a set of mapped contact sites on the 5′ SLA RNA to carry out N7 methylation and then repositions on the 5′ RNA to complete the 2′O methylation step [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The 2′-O methylation modification of the flavivirus cap protects genomes from restriction by innate immune response IFIT family members [CITATION_6] ) and N7 methylation functions to enhance viral translation [CITATION_7] ).",
